Four of the world's ethical leaders are to deliver the 11th Desmond Tutu International Peace Lecture, on Archbishop Emeritus Desmond Tutu's 90th birthday on 7 October 2021 at 7 pm South African time. Join us and hear inspirational addresses from South Africa's former public protector, Thuli Madonsela; women's and children's rights activist Gra√ßa Machel; chair of The Elders Mary Robinson; and the Dalai Lama, Tibet's highest spiritual leader. The event also features the Archbishop and the Dalai Lama discussing how to find joy amid tragedy in Mission Joy: Finding Happiness in Troubled Times, a film that celebrates their spiritual leadership and decades-long friendship. The event will be online-only, due to the Covid-19 pandemic. REGISTER | 1900 South Africa | 1700 GMT      VIEW Church Service 1200 SouthAfrica | 1000 GMT     Also on October 7, a free screening celebrating the Archbishop's 90th birthday to support the educational nonprofit Tutu Desk of the 'Children of Life' documentary. The event includes a Q&A with Tutu Desk CEO Thandeka Tutu-Gxashe & civil rights historian Danita Mason-Hogans: VIEW | 1900 EDT | 2300 GMT Read more about the Tutu Desk Campaign